<RefNameDiv>
<RefName><command>taskotop</command></RefName>
<RefPurpose>
utility to monitor what taskomatic deamon is doing.
</RefPurpose>
</RefNameDiv>

<RefSynopsisDiv>
<Synopsis>
    <cmdsynopsis>
        <command>taskotop</command>
    </cmdsynopsis>
</Synopsis>
</RefSynopsisDiv>

<RefSect1><Title>Description</Title>
    <para>
        <emphasis>taskotop</emphasis> - utility display currently running tasks in taskomatic.<sbr>
        Currently taskotop provides following information:<sbr>
        RUN ID - unique ID of the run. An ID can be used to obtain additional information. If a specific task produced any standard output or error output during its run, it can be found in /var/log/rhn/tasko/sat/*/*_RUN_ID_{out,err}.<sbr>
        TASK NAME - name of taskomatic task as shown on Admin/Task Schedules taskomatic bunch details.<sbr>
        ELAPSED TIME - displays info for how long the task has been running.<sbr>
        CHANNEL - valid for channel-repodata task in running state, shows label of the channel for which taskomatic is currently processing data.<sbr>
        General taskomatic log file can be found at /var/log/rhn/rhn_taskomatic_daemon.log
    </para>
</RefSect1>

<RefSect1><Title>Options</Title>
<variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>-h, --help</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>Display the help screen with a list of options.</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</RefSect1>

